cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DB 

The paper deals with differential privacy mechanism design, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The proposed mechanism is tailored for matrix-valued query functions, which involves matrix analysis and linear algebra (cs.LG). The paper also involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) in the design of the mechanism. Finally, the experiments involve privacy-sensitive datasets, which suggests a connection to database systems (cs.DB).
